android.permission.ACCESS_COARSE_LOCATIO.description: Access coarse location sources, such as the mobile network database, to determine an approximate phone location, where available. Malicious applications can use this to determine approximately where you are.

android.permission.ACCESS_FINE_LOCATION.description: Access fine location sources, such as the Global Positioning System on the phone, where available. Malicious applications can use this to determine where you are and may consume additional battery power.

android.permission.READ_PHONE_STATE.description: Allows the application to access the phone features of the device. An application with this permission can determine the phone number and serial number of this phone, whether a call is active, the number that call is connected to and so on.

android.permission.CAMERA.description: Allows application to take pictures and videos with the camera. This allows the application to collect images that the camera is seeing at any time.

android.permission.WRITE_EXTERNAL_STORAG.description: Allows an application to write to the SD card.

android.permission.VIBRATE.description: Allows the application to control the vibrator.

android.permission.READ_CONTACTS.description: Allows an application to read all of the contact (address) data stored on your phone. Malicious applications can use this to send your data to other people.

android.permission.USE_BIOMETRIC.description: Allows an app to use device supported biometric modalities.

android.permission.RECEIVE_BOOT_COMPLETE.description: Allows an application to start itself as soon as the system has finished booting. This can make it take longer to start the phone and allow the application to slow down the overall phone by always running.

android.permission.RECORD_AUDIO.description: Allows application to access the audio record path.

android.permission.MODIFY_AUDIO_SETTINGS.description: Allows application to modify global audio settings, such as volume and routing.

android.permission.WAKE_LOCK.description: Allows an application to prevent the phone from going to sleep.

android.permission.CHANGE_NETWORK_STATE.description: Allows an application to change the state of network connectivity.

android.permission.SYSTEM_ALERT_WINDOW.description: Allows an application to show system-alert windows. Malicious applications can take over the entire screen of the phone.

android.permission.FLASHLIGHT.description: Allows the application to control the flashlight.

android.permission.CHANGE_WIFI_STATE.description: Allows an application to connect to and disconnect from Wi-Fi access points and to make changes to configured Wi-Fi networks.

"txtAboutHtml" : "

about the application

K&H knablibom is a mobile banking application that offers you quick and comfortable way to manage your most important daily finances, and also provides you useful information about your bank accounts, bank cards or credit cards.

The application is compatible with the following devices:
  • iPhone devices, having minimum iOS 11 operation system version;
  • Smartphones with android operation system, having minimum android 5 on them

The function requiring authentication can only be access by K&H Bank clients who have a K&H e-bank contract.

You need internet connection to access the functions about your personal finances. You can access though in offline mode the K&H e-bank login and e-bank transaction signing functions.

The login process uses a built-in mobil-token, which has to be activated before the first usage. User can authenticate himself/herself with mPIN code or with biometric id on those devices where it is available. Using the application user can use the same authentication to log in to K&H e-bank and sign transactions there.

User rights are identical to the K&H e-bank rights for business clients.

You can download and use K&H knablibom application on several devices after activating each of them.

Deactivation of the application can be done by deleting the mobil-token in the settings menu. After deactivation the functions requiring authentication will not be available. In case of lost or stolen phone, you can immediately delete your mobil-token in your K&H e-bank or by calling K&H TeleCenter.

The application provides the following services:
  • login to K&H e-bank;
  • sign transactions in K&H e-bank;
  • detailed information on your bank accounts and savings accounts;
  • initiate domestic HUF payments – to already registered accounts or to new beneficiaries;
  • mobilephone balance top-up;
  • FX transfer between own accounts;
  • cheque payments;
  • detailed information on your past or pending transactions;
  • modify or delete signable and pending payments
  • check the details of your bankcards or credit cards, manage daily bankcard limits (cash withdrawal, POS purchase and internet (virtual) transactions);
  • initiate your monthly credit card repayment;
  • with the ATM and branch locator you can find the closest branch or ATM if you need personal assistance or cash;
  • read or send messages directly from the knablibom;
  • contact us through an authenticated channel via quickcall.
  • cash loan request (only available in Hungarian language)
  • card management (activate, suspend, cancel card);
  • view PIN;
  • mobile wallet;
  • Strong Customer Authentication (SCA).

K&H knablibom software is owned by K&H Bank Zrt. and it can only be used according to the conditions defined in the General Contracting Terms and Conditions applicable to banking services with electronic identification. This document can be viewed at: www.mycompany.hu site.


personal data processing information on the K&H knablibom application

Please be aware that, subject to your consent, our K&H knablibom application may access the geographic location information (hereinafter: geolocation) on your mobile device to identify your actual location.

The ATM search function of the application uses these data to identify the bank branch and/or ATM nearest to you. The geolocation data required for this function are not stored in the Bank’s own systems.

After the application has been activated, however, your geolocation data will be stored for the purpose of preventing and investigating fraud in the following cases, provided that you have authorised access and not cancelled it subsequently: activation of the knablibom application; logging on to the application; and authenticating transactions. (For example, a transaction initiated in Budapest followed by another in a foreign country at almost the same time may be indicative of data fraud.)

The Bank does not regularly collect geolocation data, nor does it use such data for purposes other than those specified above.

Your geolocation data will only be disclosed to the Bank’s employees involved in operating the application, investigating frauds or performing the services provided to you. The Bank will store such data for the duration permitted by the applicable legislation (up to eight years after the termination of your relationship with the Bank), after which it will be deleted.

Please be aware that if you are using Android 6.0 or higher as your operating system, you can allow or block access to your geolocation data by knablibom specifically. We recommend that you only allow access if you consent to data processing as described above.

If you are using an Android operating system lower than 6.0 you can only block access to your geolocation data by knablibom by disabling the relevant function completely on your mobile device. In this case you should only use a geographical location function and the knablibom application simultaneously if you consent to our processing your data as described above.

You may request information about data processing, and at any time request that your data are corrected or deleted, or terminate the service, or raise an objection against our processing of your data by contacting us by any of the means set out on mycompany.hu. Complaints concerning data processing may be filed with the Bank’s data protection officer, the Hungarian National Authority for Data Protection and Freedom of Information or the competent court. The Bank’s data protection registration number is 00465.
